title: USA Today Co. - Wikipedia
snippet: USA Today Co., Inc., known until 2025 as Gannett Co., Inc. (/ɡəˈnɛt/ gə-NET), is an American mass media holding company headquartered in New York City. snippet: Gannett's portfolio also includes digital marketing solutions brand, LocaliQ, and the events division, USA Today Network Ventures. Gannett was founded by Frank E. Gannett in 1906 and is headquartered in New York, NY.

title: USA Today Owner Gannett Moves HQ from VA to the Theater District
snippet: Gannett, the nation’s largest newspaper publisher which owns USA Today and more than 250 local newspapers from Phoenix to Rochester, is packing up its corporate headquarters in Tysons, Virginia and moving it to New York City.
